snippet.textDisplay:
In my 1988 Audi 100...
My manual wheel bolt fastener for changing tires on the roadside has a formed tip on the long arm, with rubber insert to screw in and remove the plugs without dropping.


Also it has a Keihin I carburator, manual choke, aaaand came with a unregulated cat-converter...

also its runs with the worst fuel available (low compression) and is a freerunner, so if belts go bang, there is no pistons banging on the valves..


fuel pump is piston operated at the block, there is no real fuel pressure regulator but a bubble-catch-tank befor the carb.

4cyl / 1766ccm with humongous 66kW (at the engine..) but really nice fuel economy.


also 160bar-ish hydraulic brake and steering support, with backup pressure tank for multiple braking even after engine off.


It is basically the VW Golf Engine and half of the later used V8
